    Scope and Contents
Papers of John Keiser, member of SSU History faculty, 1970-1978, and Vice-President for Academic Affairs, 1971-1978.Speech drafts, official memos, letters, tenure self-evaluations, and clippings concerning Keiser's career as a SSU history professor and in SSU administration. Includes Keiser's hard-bound compilation of his addresses to faculty (1971-1978), a hard-bound, unpublished manuscript describing faculty unrest at Eastern Illinois University (where Keiser taught before his career at SSU), as well as his remarks presented at each of SSU commencements, 1972-1978 (tipped into each respective commencement booklet).Three anti-Keiser faculty protest placards are included in this collection are foldered on the shelf next to box 1. A commemorative paperwieght (Lincoln Land Community College groundbreaking, 1970) included in the donation was transferred to V1 Artifacts Collection.See also J1/1/6  
  
